%S A394430 1,8,24,32,44,48,56,64,80,84,92,104,116,120,128,132,140,144,160,164,
%T A394430 168,176,184,200,204,208,212,216,220,224,252,260,264,288,296,300,320,
%U A394430 324,328,332,344,356,360,368,380,384,392,416,424,440,444,452,464,468,476,480,492,504,512,524
%N A394430 Totient numbers k for which there does not exist an m = p^e or 2*p^e, p an odd prime and e >= 1, such that phi(m) = k.
%C A394430 Totient numbers k such that the cyclic group C_k does not appear as the group of units of a ring Z/rZ.
%H A394430 Miles Englezou, <a href="/A394430/b394430.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A394430 Max Alekseyev, <a href="https://oeis.org/wiki/User:Max_Alekseyev/gpscripts">PARI/GP Scripts for Miscellaneous Math Problems</a> (invphi.gp).
%e A394430 8 is a term since phi(m) = 8 for m in {15, 16, 20, 24, 30} and none of these m are an odd prime power or twice an odd prime power.
%e A394430 24 is a term since phi(m) = 24 for m in {35, 39, 45, 52, 56, 70, 72, 78, 84, 90} and none of these m are an odd prime power or twice an odd prime power.
%o A394430 (PARI) isok(n) = istotient(n) && select(y -> y==[n], Set(apply(x -> znstar(x)[2], invphi(n))))==[] \\ using _Max Alekseyev_'s invphi.gp; see link
%Y A394430 Cf. A000010, A002202.
%K A394430 nonn,new
%O A394430 1,2
